revision.text:
{{inline|date=November 2018}} [[Image:Cattedrale di noyon.jpg|thumb|right|250px|[[Noyon Cathedral]]]] The former French Catholic '''diocese of Noyon''' lay in the north-east of France, around [[Noyon]]. It was formed when [[Saint Medardus]] moved the seat of the bishopric at [[Vermandois]] to Noyon, in the sixth century. For four centuries it was united with the [[bishopric of Tournai]]. Then in the twelfth century it was again independent, and the bishop of Noyon became a ''[[peer of France|pairie-comté]]'' of France.
The diocese of Noyon was brought to an end by the [[French Revolution]]. Its territory passed to the [[diocese of Beauvais]].
