'''Arturo Salazar Mejía''' (April 11, 1921 – November 1, 2009) was the [[Roman Catholic]] bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Pasto]], [[Colombia]].

Ordained on February 6, 1944, Salazar Mejía was made a  bishop by [[Pope Paul VI]] on October 14, 1965 and was ordained on January 6, 1966 retiring on February 6, 1995.<ref>{{Catholic-hierarchy|bishop|bsalm|Bishop Arturo Salazar Mejia, O.A.R.|21 January 2015}}</ref>

