{{Infobox royalty | name = Dabuya | title = [[Ispahbadh]] of [[Tabaristan]] | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | succession = | reign = 660-712 | predecessor = [[Gil Gavbara]] | regent = | successor = [[Farrukhan the Great]] | spouse = | spouse-type = | issue = | full name = | house = [[Dabuyid dynasty]] | father = [[Gil Gavbara]] | mother = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = 712 | death_place = [[Tabaristan]] | religion = [[Zoroastrianism]] }} '''Dabuya''' or '''Dabuyih''' ({{lang-fa|دابویه}}), was the [[Dabuyid]] ruler ([[ispahbadh]]) of [[Tabaristan]]. He succeeded his father [[Gil Gavbara]] in 660 and reigned until his death in 712. His son, [[Farrukhan the Great]] succeeded him.
