{{italic title}} '''''La Nation française''''' ("The French Nation") was a French [[Monarchism|monarchist]] weekly magazine influenced by [[Charles Maurras]], the founder of the [[Action française]] movement.<ref name="jond">{{cite book|author=Jonathan Dewald|title=Lost Worlds: The Emergence of French Social History, 1815-1970|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tjal1JUzoLkC&pg=PA142|accessdate=18 June 2015|date=1 November 2010|publisher=Penn State Press|isbn=0-271-04781-X|page=142}}</ref> It was founded in 1955<ref name="oli">{{cite web|author=Olivier Véron|title=L’Héritage de la Nation Française (en préparation)|url=http://www.lesprovinciales.fr/L-Heritage-de-la-Nation-Francaise.html|work=Les provinciales|accessdate=25 August 2016|language=French}}</ref> as an [[Spin-off (media)|offshoot]] of ''[[Aspects de la France]]'', another monarchist review founded in June 1947 by [[Maurice Pujo]] and [[Georges Calzant]], former members of the Action Française who continued to support the [[nationalism|nationalist]] monarchist current.<ref>{{cite book|author=J. A. Laponce|title=The Government of the Fifth Republic: French Political Parties and the Constitution|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=vrZrVZvTDuYC&pg=PA396|accessdate=18 June 2015|year=1961|publisher=University of California Press|page=396|id=GGKEY:KGRNN62B34H}}</ref> Directed by journalist [[Pierre Boutang]],<ref name=jond/><ref>{{cite book|author=Leah Anderst|title=The Films of Eric Rohmer: French New Wave to Old Master|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RBztAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA122|accessdate=18 June 2015|date=13 March 2014|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|isbn=978-1-137-01100-8|page=122}}</ref> others writers include: [[Jean de La Varende]], [[Antoine Blondin]], [[Roger Nimier]], [[Philippe Ariès]] or [[Gabriel Matzneff]]. ''La Nation française'' supported [[Henri, Count of Paris (1908–1999)|Henri of Orléans]], "count of Paris." After having defended "French Algeria" during the [[Algerian War]] (1954–62), it dissolved itself, on disagreements in particular concerning Boutang's "compromission" with [[Charles de Gaulle]].<ref>[http://www.chez.com/cuved/publi/courantsfafs.htm Les courants de l’extrême droite française] {{fr icon}}</ref> The magazine ceased publication in 1967.<ref name="oli"/>
