'''Obi divination''' is a system of [[divination]] used in the traditional [[Yoruba religion]] and in Yoruba-derived [[Afro-American religions]].<ref>{{cite web|title=BASIC OBI ABATA DIVINATION|url=http://api.ning.com/files/5AMBu4bEFAeV3xPCBqF-ekp5qQ4ZuYF6zVp0xdyFitI_/bas_obi.pdf|website=http://api.ning.com/files/5AMBu4bEFAeV3xPCBqF-ekp5qQ4ZuYF6zVp0xdyFitI_/bas_obi.pdf|accessdate=28 November 2014}}</ref> In [[Yorubaland]], it uses palm or [[kola nut]]s; in [[Latin America]] and the [[Caribbean]] it uses four pieces of [[coconut]].
